<subSubSection box="[151,264,583,609]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,517,546,609]" box="[151,264,583,609]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,256,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Figure 4</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,654,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species is readily distinguishable from others in the genus by the short crown with evenly rounded anterior margin and by the elongate, arched aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,726,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Description</emphasis>
. Length of male 
<quantity box="[532,621,726,753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
. Color pale stramineous, frontoclypeus, basolateral triangles of mesonotum and median area of mesonotum and scutellum pale ochraceous. Crown in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1275,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin evenly rounded, subparallel to posterior margin, median length less than width between eyes. Forewing with second apical cell petiolate (
<figureCitation box="[469,560,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
Male 2S apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[437,529,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) short and rounded. Pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation box="[939,1027,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
) with small but distinct sclerotized rounded tooth posteroventrally. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[699,785,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) moderately long with 4-5 macrosetae, apex oblique. Style preapical lobe rounded, apophysis footlike apically with short toe and rounded heel (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1188,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft elongate, slender, evenly arched in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[648,736,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
) with preapical processes short and well separated from apex, apical processes relatively long, acuminate and extended ventrobasad relative to shaft apex. Gonopore preapical on posterior surface adjacent to tips of distal processes (
<figureCitation box="[743,834,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,938,962]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,188,909]" captionTargetId="figure-15@7.[151,1436,181,914]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Mayawa brevicephala sp. nov., male holotype. A–B, lateral and dorsal habitus; C, head and anterior part of thorax, anterior view; D, base of abdomen, ventral view; E–F, genital capsule, lateral and ventral view; G, genitalia, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; H, genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4556775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4556775/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1225,1087,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,654,1221]" box="[199,1225,1087,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1087,1113]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is a Latinized adjective referring to the relatively short head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
